JOHANNESBURG - Consumer Price Inflation (CPI) slowed dropped to its lowest level since March 2015 down to 4.4 percent in January 2018, from 4.7 percent in December 2017. StatSA said food and non-alcoholic beverages contributed 0.2 of a percentage to the decline. A drop in transport prices contributed 0.1 of a percentage point and miscellaneous goods and services contributing 0.1 of a percentage point to the drop. The CPI drop is good news for consumers and could encourage the Reserve Bank to drop interest rates. eNCA